set.seed(0)

N <- nrow(Auto)
tr <- sample(1:N, round(N/2), replace = FALSE)
Auto.tr <- Auto[tr,]
Auto.val <- Auto[-tr,]

mse <- rep(NA, 10)
for ( p in 1:10 ) {
  fit <- lm(mpg ~ poly(horsepower, p), data = Auto.tr)
  mse[p] <- mean((predict(fit, Auto.val) - Auto.val$mpg)^2)
}
plot(1:10, mse, type = "b", pch = 19, col = 2, ylim = c(12, 32),
     xlab = "Degree of polynomial", ylab = "Mean squared error")

K-fold Cross Validation


  • LOOCV K-fold Cross Validation (K-fold CV)


  1. \(K\) (e.g., \(K=5\), or \(K=10\))

  2. fold \(K-1\) fold () . fold () MSE

  3. fold , \(K-1\) fold . \(K\)

  4. \(K\) MSE cross-validated MSE . test MSE

\[ \text{CV}_{(K)} = \frac{1}{K}\sum_{k=1}^K \text{MSE}_k \]


Auto : LOOCV K-fold CV

  • Auto ,

  • LOOCV

mse <- rep(0, 10)
for ( p in 1:10 ) {
  for ( i in 1:N ) {
    tr <- Auto[-i,]
    te <- Auto[i,]
    fit <- lm(mpg ~ poly(horsepower, p), data = tr)
    mse[p] <- mse[p] + (predict(fit, te) - te$mpg)^2
  }
}
mse <- mse/N

plot(1:10, mse, type = "l", lwd = 3, ylim = c(12, 32), main = "LOOCV",
     xlab = "Degree of polynomial", ylab = "Mean squared error")

  • K-fold CV
set.seed(0)

K <- 10
M <- round(N/K)
V <- matrix(0, K, 2)
for ( k in 1:K ) {
  V[k,] <- c(M*(k - 1) + 1, min(M*k, N))
}

ind <- sample(1:N)
mse <- matrix(NA, K, 10)
for ( k in 1:K ) {
  val <- ind[V[k, 1]:V[k, 2]]
  tr <- ind[-(V[k, 1]:V[k, 2])]
  for ( p in 1:10 ) {
    fit <- lm(mpg ~ poly(horsepower, p), data = Auto, subset = tr)
    mse[k, p] <- mean((predict(fit, Auto[val,]) - Auto$mpg[val])^2)
  }
}
CV <- colMeans(mse)
print((1:10)[which.min(CV)])
## [1] 7
plot(1:10, CV, type = "l", lwd = 3, ylim = c(12, 32), 
     main = paste(k, "-fold CV", sep = ""),
     xlab = "Degree of polynomial", ylab = "Mean squared error")

for ( j in 2:10 ) {
  ind <- sample(1:N)
  mse <- matrix(NA, K, 10)
  for ( k in 1:K ) {
    val <- ind[V[k, 1]:V[k, 2]]
    tr <- ind[-(V[k, 1]:V[k, 2])]
    for ( p in 1:10 ) {
      fit <- lm(mpg ~ poly(horsepower, p), data = Auto, subset = tr)
      mse[k, p] <- mean((predict(fit, Auto[val,]) - Auto$mpg[val])^2)
    }
  }
  CV <- colMeans(mse)
  print((1:10)[which.min(CV)])
  lines(1:10, CV, lwd = 3, col = j)
}

library(boot)
set.seed(0)
cv <- rep(NA, 10)
for ( p in 1:10 ) {
  fit <- glm(mpg ~ poly(horsepower, p), data = Auto)
  cv[p] <- cv.glm(Auto, fit, K = 10)$delta[1]  # K   LOOCV
}
plot(1:10, cv, type = "b", col = 2, pch = 19, 
     xlab = "Degree of polynomial", ylab = "MSE")

Bootstrap

Motivating example: Portfolio 

library(ISLR)
plot(Portfolio, col = "darkgreen", pch = 20)

    • \((\alpha, \,\,1-\alpha)\)

    • \(X\), \(Y\) \(R\) \(R = \alpha X + (1-\alpha) Y\)

    • \(\text{Var}(R)\) \(\alpha\) \[ \alpha^* = \frac{\sigma_Y^2 - \sigma_{XY}}{\sigma_X^2 + \sigma_Y^2 - 2\sigma_{XY}}\]

    • \(\alpha\) 

MVP <- function(X, Y) (var(Y) - cov(X, Y))/(var(X) + var(Y) - 2*cov(X, Y))
print(alpha <- MVP(Portfolio$X, Portfolio$Y))
## [1] 0.5758321
  • . \(\alpha\) .

  1. resampling() (\(B\))

  2. \(\alpha\)

  3. 2 \(\alpha\) \(\alpha\) 

set.seed(0)

B <- 5000
alpha.boot <- rep(NA, B)
N <- nrow(Portfolio)

for ( b in 1:B ) {
  Portfolio.boot <- Portfolio[sample(1:N, N, replace = TRUE),] 
  alpha.boot[b] <- with(Portfolio.boot, MVP(X, Y))
}

hist(alpha.boot, probability = TRUE, xlab = expression(alpha), 
     col = "lightgray", border = "white", nclass = 100,
     main = "Bootstrap distribution")
abline(v = alpha, col = 2)
